    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Crankshaft Main Bearing Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "387_3.0_jpn_11582909_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Attach the upper bearing to the block, paying attention to the positional relationship between the main bearing oil hole (A) and the block oil hole (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The upper bearing must be a grooved bearing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The lower bearing shall be a groove-free bearing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "387_3.0_jpn_11582910_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Measure the distance (A, B) between the upper and lower crankshaft main bearings and both ends of the journal section, and confirm that the difference between the measured values is within the standard values."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Standard value:"
          },
          {
            "text": "-0.5－+0.5mm"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When a new bearing is assembled, it should be broken in at idle for 10-20 minutes to prevent separation or seizure of the bearing if the rotation is increased too rapidly."
      ]
    }
  ],
